I think the formula definitions of Precision and Recall in 2-4-Logistic are not correct, compared with what tells me on sklearn Doc and Wikipedia.

Confusion Matrix
There is also a problem that appears in the picture of Confusion Matrix. (I did not fix the picture in the commit)

The Actual Values should be presented by axis 0 and Predicted Values in axis 1. So that calculation results can match the classification_report with the correct definition of precision and recall.
Finally, The correct matrix should be:









TP
FN


FP
TN



See Confusion Matrix in sklearn and Wiki.

Added Hindi translation for 1-Introduction base README.md.
Issue Reference

Consider the following sentence in 4-Classification/README.md:
In this section, you will build on the skills you learned in the first part of this curriculum all about regression to learn about other classifiers you can use that will help you learn about your data.
It is unclear and hard to understand. I propose rephrasing it to
In this section, you will build on the skills you learned in the first part of this curriculum on regression, and learn about other classifiers that you can use to better understand the data.
which conveys the intended meaning in a much simpler way.
PS: I was working on translating this section into Hindi and found that the original phrasing in English was quite hard to make sense of. Also updated Cassie's Twitter handle as it has changed. Please review and merge if the proposed change seems to improve the understanding.
Thanks.

Heyy, I added the translation for five NLP files (section 6). I wish I could translate the other files too, but I think I need a little break from that :D. Turns out the syntactical rules are quite different between English and Portuguese, which makes translating really tricky. I did my best to stick to the original text, while also writing something that makes sense to Brazilians and respects our rules. Let me know if something needs to be changed.

The following passage is factually wrong. No "unnecessary word" was added in original the French translation. What you're reading is just the next sentence in the book, joined with a comma (see below). While I understand the utilitarian, educational goal of this example, it is disparaging to criticize a totally fine translation like this. Maybe this could be edited and replaced with a made-up alternative translation, intentionally worded in order to be inaccurate?
"However little known the feelings or views of such a man may be on his first entering a neighbourhood, this truth is so well fixed in the minds of the surrounding families, that he is considered the rightful property of some one or other of their daughters."
